  "prompt": "Why is Quora still ad-free?",
  "response": "As of the last update, Quora is not entirely ad-free. While Quora remained ad-free for many years after its launch in 2009, it eventually introduced advertising as a revenue model. Quora Ads started appearing around 2016 as a way for the company to monetize its platform while maintaining the quality and relevance of its content.\n\nQuora employs various monetization strategies, including ads, partnerships, and its subscription service, Quora+. The decision to introduce advertisements was driven by the need to generate revenue to support and expand the platform while still ensuring that the core user experience remains focused on high-quality content and engagement.\n\nThe information may have changed since then, so it is advisable to check the latest updates from Quora directly for the most current details regarding its business model and advertising practices.",
